234 /// Get .debug_loc entry for the instruction range starting at MI. ----
235 static DbgValueLoc getDebugLocValue(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
236 const DIExpression *Expr = MI->getDebugExpression(); 0
237 const bool IsVariadic = MI->isDebugValueList(); 0
238 assert(MI->getNumOperands() >= 3); 0
239 SmallVector DbgValueLocEntries; 0
240 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI->debug_operands()) { 0
241 if (Op.isReg()) { 0
242 MachineLocation MLoc(Op.getReg(), 0
243 MI->isNonListDebugValue() && MI->isDebugOffsetImm()); 0
244 DbgValueLocEntries.push_back(DbgValueLocEntry(MLoc)); 0
245 } else if (Op.isTargetIndex()) { 0
246 DbgValueLocEntries.push_back( 0
247 DbgValueLocEntry(TargetIndexLocation(Op.getIndex(), Op.getOffset()))); 0
248 } else if (Op.isImm()) 0
249 DbgValueLocEntries.push_back(DbgValueLocEntry(Op.getImm())); 0
250 else if (Op.isFPImm()) 0
251 DbgValueLocEntries.push_back(DbgValueLocEntry(Op.getFPImm())); 0
252 else if (Op.isCImm()) 0
253 DbgValueLocEntries.push_back(DbgValueLocEntry(Op.getCImm())); 0
254 else ----
255 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected debug operand in DBG_VALUE* instruction!"); 0
256 } ----
257 return DbgValueLoc(Expr, DbgValueLocEntries, IsVariadic); 0
258 } 0

304 // non-fragment entries for the same variable at different frame indices. ----

501 ----
502 if (!SP->isDefinition()) 0
503 return; 0
504 ----
505 if (SP->getName() != "") 0
506 addAccelName(CU, SP->getName(), Die); 0
507 ----
508 // If the linkage name is different than the name, go ahead and output that as ----
509 // well into the name table. Only do that if we are going to actually emit ----
510 // that name. ----
511 if (SP->getLinkageName() != "" && SP->getName() != SP->getLinkageName() && 0
512 (useAllLinkageNames() || InfoHolder.getAbstractScopeDIEs().lookup(SP))) 0
513 addAccelName(CU, SP->getLinkageName(), Die); 0
514 ----
515 // If this is an Objective-C selector name add it to the ObjC accelerator ----
516 // too. ----
517 if (isObjCClass(SP->getName())) { 0
518 StringRef Class, Category; 0
519 getObjCClassCategory(SP->getName(), Class, Category); 0
520 addAccelObjC(CU, Class, Die); 0
521 if (Category != "") 0
522 addAccelObjC(CU, Category, Die); 0
523 // Also add the base method name to the name table. ----
524 addAccelName(CU, getObjCMethodName(SP->getName()), Die); 0
525 } ----
526 } ----
527 ----
528 /// Check whether we should create a DIE for the given Scope, return true ----
529 /// if we don't create a DIE (the corresponding DIE is null). ----
530 bool DwarfDebug::isLexicalScopeDIENull(LexicalScope *Scope) { 0
531 if (Scope->isAbstractScope()) 0
532 return false; 0
533 ----
534 // We don't create a DIE if there is no Range. ----
535 const SmallVectorImpl &Ranges = Scope->getRanges(); 0
536 if (Ranges.empty()) 0
537 return true; 0
538 ----
539 if (Ranges.size() > 1) 0
540 return false; 0
541 ----
542 // We don't create a DIE if we have a single Range and the end label ----
543 // is null. ----
544 return !getLabelAfterInsn(Ranges.front().second); 0
545 } ----

557 ----
558 void DwarfDebug::constructAbstractSubprogramScopeDIE(DwarfCompileUnit &SrcCU, 0
559 LexicalScope *Scope) { ----
560 assert(Scope && Scope->getScopeNode()); 0
561 assert(Scope->isAbstractScope()); 0
562 assert(!Scope->getInlinedAt()); 0
563 ----
564 auto *SP = cast(Scope->getScopeNode()); 0
565 ----
566 // Find the subprogram's DwarfCompileUnit in the SPMap in case the subprogram ----
567 // was inlined from another compile unit. ----
568 if (useSplitDwarf() && !shareAcrossDWOCUs() && !SP->getUnit()->getSplitDebugInlining()) 0
569 // Avoid building the original CU if it won't be used ----
570 SrcCU.constructAbstractSubprogramScopeDIE(Scope); 0
571 else { ----
572 auto &CU = getOrCreateDwarfCompileUnit(SP->getUnit()); 0
573 if (auto *SkelCU = CU.getSkeleton()) { 0
574 (shareAcrossDWOCUs() ? CU : SrcCU) 0
575 .constructAbstractSubprogramScopeDIE(Scope); 0
576 if (CU.getCUNode()->getSplitDebugInlining()) 0
577 SkelCU->constructAbstractSubprogramScopeDIE(Scope); 0
578 } else ----
579 CU.constructAbstractSubprogramScopeDIE(Scope); 0
580 } ----
581 } 0
582 ----
583 /// Represents a parameter whose call site value can be described by applying a ----
584 /// debug expression to a register in the forwarded register worklist. ----
585 struct FwdRegParamInfo { ----
586 /// The described parameter register. ----
587 unsigned ParamReg; ----
588 ----
589 /// Debug expression that has been built up when walking through the ----
590 /// instruction chain that produces the parameter's value. ----
591 const DIExpression *Expr; ----
592 }; ----
593 ----
594 /// Register worklist for finding call site values. ----
595 using FwdRegWorklist = MapVector>; ----
596 /// Container for the set of registers known to be clobbered on the path to a ----
597 /// call site. ----
598 using ClobberedRegSet = SmallSet; ----
599 ----
600 /// Append the expression \p Addition to \p Original and return the result. ----
601 static const DIExpression *combineDIExpressions(const DIExpression *Original, 0
602 const DIExpression *Addition) { ----
603 std::vector Elts = Addition->getElements().vec(); 0
604 // Avoid multiple DW_OP_stack_values. ----
605 if (Original->isImplicit() && Addition->isImplicit()) 0
606 erase_value(Elts, dwarf::DW_OP_stack_value); 0
607 const DIExpression *CombinedExpr = ----
608 (Elts.size() > 0) ? DIExpression::append(Original, Elts) : Original; 0
609 return CombinedExpr; 0
610 } 0
611 ----
612 /// Emit call site parameter entries that are described by the given value and ----
613 /// debug expression. ----
614 template ----
615 static void finishCallSiteParams(ValT Val, const DIExpression *Expr, 0
616 ArrayRef DescribedParams, ----
617 ParamSet &Params) { ----
618 for (auto Param : DescribedParams) { 0
619 bool ShouldCombineExpressions = Expr && Param.Expr->getNumElements() > 0; 0
620 ----
621 // TODO: Entry value operations can currently not be combined with any ----
622 // other expressions, so we can't emit call site entries in those cases. ----
623 if (ShouldCombineExpressions && Expr->isEntryValue()) 0
624 continue; 0
625 ----
626 // If a parameter's call site value is produced by a chain of ----
627 // instructions we may have already created an expression for the ----
628 // parameter when walking through the instructions. Append that to the ----
629 // base expression. ----
630 const DIExpression *CombinedExpr = 0
631 ShouldCombineExpressions ? combineDIExpressions(Expr, Param.Expr) 0
632 : Expr; ----
633 assert((!CombinedExpr || CombinedExpr->isValid()) && 0
634 "Combined debug expression is invalid"); ----
635 ----
636 DbgValueLoc DbgLocVal(CombinedExpr, DbgValueLocEntry(Val)); 0
637 DbgCallSiteParam CSParm(Param.ParamReg, DbgLocVal); 0
638 Params.push_back(CSParm); 0
639 ++NumCSParams; 0
640 } ----
641 } 0
642 ----
643 /// Add \p Reg to the worklist, if it's not already present, and mark that the ----
644 /// given parameter registers' values can (potentially) be described using ----
645 /// that register and an debug expression. ----
646 static void addToFwdRegWorklist(FwdRegWorklist &Worklist, unsigned Reg, 0
647 const DIExpression *Expr, ----
648 ArrayRef ParamsToAdd) { ----
649 auto I = Worklist.insert({Reg, {}}); 0
650 auto &ParamsForFwdReg = I.first->second; 0
651 for (auto Param : ParamsToAdd) { 0
652 assert(none_of(ParamsForFwdReg, 0
653 [Param](const FwdRegParamInfo &D) { ----
654 return D.ParamReg == Param.ParamReg; ----
655 }) && ----
656 "Same parameter described twice by forwarding reg"); ----
657 ----
658 // If a parameter's call site value is produced by a chain of ----
659 // instructions we may have already created an expression for the ----
660 // parameter when walking through the instructions. Append that to the ----
661 // new expression. ----
662 const DIExpression *CombinedExpr = combineDIExpressions(Expr, Param.Expr); 0
663 ParamsForFwdReg.push_back({Param.ParamReg, CombinedExpr}); 0
664 } ----
665 } 0
666 ----
667 /// Interpret values loaded into registers by \p CurMI. ----
668 static void interpretValues(const MachineInstr *CurMI, 0
669 FwdRegWorklist &ForwardedRegWorklist, ----
670 ParamSet &Params, ----
671 ClobberedRegSet &ClobberedRegUnits) { ----
672 ----
673 const MachineFunction *MF = CurMI->getMF(); 0
674 const DIExpression *EmptyExpr = ----
675 DIExpression::get(MF->getFunction().getContext(), {}); 0
676 const auto &TRI = *MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
677 const auto &TII = *MF->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
678 const auto &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
679 ----
680 // If an instruction defines more than one item in the worklist, we may run ----
681 // into situations where a worklist register's value is (potentially) ----
682 // described by the previous value of another register that is also defined ----
683 // by that instruction. ----
684 // ----
685 // This can for example occur in cases like this: ----
686 // ----
687 // $r1 = mov 123 ----
688 // $r0, $r1 = mvrr $r1, 456 ----
689 // call @foo, $r0, $r1 ----
690 // ----
691 // When describing $r1's value for the mvrr instruction, we need to make sure ----
692 // that we don't finalize an entry value for $r0, as that is dependent on the ----
693 // previous value of $r1 (123 rather than 456). ----
694 // ----
695 // In order to not have to distinguish between those cases when finalizing ----
696 // entry values, we simply postpone adding new parameter registers to the ----
697 // worklist, by first keeping them in this temporary container until the ----
698 // instruction has been handled. ----
699 FwdRegWorklist TmpWorklistItems; 0
700 ----
701 // If the MI is an instruction defining one or more parameters' forwarding ----
702 // registers, add those defines. ----
703 ClobberedRegSet NewClobberedRegUnits; 0
704 auto getForwardingRegsDefinedByMI = [&](const MachineInstr &MI, 0
705 SmallSetVector &Defs) { ----
706 if (MI.isDebugInstr()) 0
707 return; 0
708 ----
709 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.all_defs()) { 0
710 if (MO.getReg().isPhysical()) { 0
711 for (auto &FwdReg : ForwardedRegWorklist) 0
712 if (TRI.regsOverlap(FwdReg.first, MO.getReg())) 0
713 Defs.insert(FwdReg.first); 0
714 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI.regunits(MO.getReg())) 0
715 NewClobberedRegUnits.insert(Unit); 0
716 } ----
717 } ----
718 }; 0
719 ----
720 // Set of worklist registers that are defined by this instruction. ----
721 SmallSetVector FwdRegDefs; 0
722 ----
723 getForwardingRegsDefinedByMI(*CurMI, FwdRegDefs); 0
724 if (FwdRegDefs.empty()) { 0
725 // Any definitions by this instruction will clobber earlier reg movements. ----
726 ClobberedRegUnits.insert(NewClobberedRegUnits.begin(), 0
727 NewClobberedRegUnits.end()); 0
728 return; 0
729 } ----
730 ----
731 // It's possible that we find a copy from a non-volatile register to the param ----
732 // register, which is clobbered in the meantime. Test for clobbered reg unit ----
733 // overlaps before completing. ----
734 auto IsRegClobberedInMeantime = [&](Register Reg) -> bool { 0
735 for (auto &RegUnit : ClobberedRegUnits) 0
736 if (TRI.hasRegUnit(Reg, RegUnit)) 0
737 return true; 0
738 return false; 0
739 }; 0
740 ----
741 for (auto ParamFwdReg : FwdRegDefs) { 0
742 if (auto ParamValue = TII.describeLoadedValue(*CurMI, ParamFwdReg)) { 0
743 if (ParamValue->first.isImm()) { 0
744 int64_t Val = ParamValue->first.getImm(); 0
745 finishCallSiteParams(Val, ParamValue->second, 0
746 ForwardedRegWorklist[ParamFwdReg], Params); 0
747 } else if (ParamValue->first.isReg()) { 0
748 Register RegLoc = ParamValue->first.getReg(); 0
749 Register SP = TLI.getStackPointerRegisterToSaveRestore(); 0
750 Register FP = TRI.getFrameRegister(*MF); 0
751 bool IsSPorFP = (RegLoc == SP) || (RegLoc == FP); 0
752 if (!IsRegClobberedInMeantime(RegLoc) && 0
753 (TRI.isCalleeSavedPhysReg(RegLoc, *MF) || IsSPorFP)) { 0
754 MachineLocation MLoc(RegLoc, /*Indirect=*/IsSPorFP); 0
755 finishCallSiteParams(MLoc, ParamValue->second, 0
756 ForwardedRegWorklist[ParamFwdReg], Params); 0
757 } else { ----
758 // ParamFwdReg was described by the non-callee saved register ----
759 // RegLoc. Mark that the call site values for the parameters are ----
760 // dependent on that register instead of ParamFwdReg. Since RegLoc ----
761 // may be a register that will be handled in this iteration, we ----
762 // postpone adding the items to the worklist, and instead keep them ----
763 // in a temporary container. ----
764 addToFwdRegWorklist(TmpWorklistItems, RegLoc, ParamValue->second, 0
765 ForwardedRegWorklist[ParamFwdReg]); 0
766 } ----
767 } ----
768 } ----
769 } ----
770 ----
771 // Remove all registers that this instruction defines from the worklist. ----
772 for (auto ParamFwdReg : FwdRegDefs) 0
773 ForwardedRegWorklist.erase(ParamFwdReg); 0
774 ----
775 // Any definitions by this instruction will clobber earlier reg movements. ----
776 ClobberedRegUnits.insert(NewClobberedRegUnits.begin(), 0
777 NewClobberedRegUnits.end()); 0
778 ----
779 // Now that we are done handling this instruction, add items from the ----
780 // temporary worklist to the real one. ----
781 for (auto &New : TmpWorklistItems) 0
782 addToFwdRegWorklist(ForwardedRegWorklist, New.first, EmptyExpr, New.second); 0
783 TmpWorklistItems.clear(); 0
784 } 0
785 ----
786 static bool interpretNextInstr(const MachineInstr *CurMI, 0
787 FwdRegWorklist &ForwardedRegWorklist, ----
788 ParamSet &Params, ----
789 ClobberedRegSet &ClobberedRegUnits) { ----
790 // Skip bundle headers. ----
791 if (CurMI->isBundle()) 0
792 return true; 0
793 ----
794 // If the next instruction is a call we can not interpret parameter's ----
795 // forwarding registers or we finished the interpretation of all ----
796 // parameters. ----
797 if (CurMI->isCall()) 0
798 return false; 0
799 ----
800 if (ForwardedRegWorklist.empty()) 0
801 return false; 0
802 ----
803 // Avoid NOP description. ----
804 if (CurMI->getNumOperands() == 0) 0
805 return true; 0
806 ----
807 interpretValues(CurMI, ForwardedRegWorklist, Params, ClobberedRegUnits); 0
808 ----
809 return true; 0
810 } ----
811 ----
812 /// Try to interpret values loaded into registers that forward parameters ----
813 /// for \p CallMI. Store parameters with interpreted value into \p Params. ----
814 static void collectCallSiteParameters(const MachineInstr *CallMI, 0
815 ParamSet &Params) { ----
816 const MachineFunction *MF = CallMI->getMF(); 0
817 const auto &CalleesMap = MF->getCallSitesInfo(); 0
818 auto CallFwdRegsInfo = CalleesMap.find(CallMI); 0
819 ----
820 // There is no information for the call instruction. ----
821 if (CallFwdRegsInfo == CalleesMap.end()) 0
822 return; 0
823 ----
824 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB = CallMI->getParent(); 0
825 ----
826 // Skip the call instruction. ----
827 auto I = std::next(CallMI->getReverseIterator()); 0
828 ----
829 FwdRegWorklist ForwardedRegWorklist; 0
830 ----
831 const DIExpression *EmptyExpr = ----
832 DIExpression::get(MF->getFunction().getContext(), {}); 0
833 ----
834 // Add all the forwarding registers into the ForwardedRegWorklist. ----
835 for (const auto &ArgReg : CallFwdRegsInfo->second) { 0
836 bool InsertedReg = ----
837 ForwardedRegWorklist.insert({ArgReg.Reg, {{ArgReg.Reg, EmptyExpr}}}) 0
838 .second; 0
839 assert(InsertedReg && "Single register used to forward two arguments?"); 0
840 (void)InsertedReg; ----
841 } ----
842 ----
843 // Do not emit CSInfo for undef forwarding registers. ----
844 for (const auto &MO : CallMI->uses()) 0
845 if (MO.isReg() && MO.isUndef()) 0
846 ForwardedRegWorklist.erase(MO.getReg()); 0
847 ----
848 // We erase, from the ForwardedRegWorklist, those forwarding registers for ----
849 // which we successfully describe a loaded value (by using ----
850 // the describeLoadedValue()). For those remaining arguments in the working ----
851 // list, for which we do not describe a loaded value by ----
852 // the describeLoadedValue(), we try to generate an entry value expression ----
853 // for their call site value description, if the call is within the entry MBB. ----
854 // TODO: Handle situations when call site parameter value can be described ----
855 // as the entry value within basic blocks other than the first one. ----
856 bool ShouldTryEmitEntryVals = MBB->getIterator() == MF->begin(); 0
857 ----
858 // Search for a loading value in forwarding registers inside call delay slot. ----
859 ClobberedRegSet ClobberedRegUnits; 0
860 if (CallMI->hasDelaySlot()) { 0
861 auto Suc = std::next(CallMI->getIterator()); 0
862 // Only one-instruction delay slot is supported. ----
863 auto BundleEnd = llvm::getBundleEnd(CallMI->getIterator()); 0
864 (void)BundleEnd; ----
865 assert(std::next(Suc) == BundleEnd && 0
866 "More than one instruction in call delay slot"); ----
867 // Try to interpret value loaded by instruction. ----
868 if (!interpretNextInstr(&*Suc, ForwardedRegWorklist, Params, ClobberedRegUnits)) 0
869 return; 0
870 } ----
871 ----
872 // Search for a loading value in forwarding registers. ----
873 for (; I != MBB->rend(); ++I) { 0
874 // Try to interpret values loaded by instruction. ----
875 if (!interpretNextInstr(&*I, ForwardedRegWorklist, Params, ClobberedRegUnits)) 0
876 return; 0
877 } ----
878 ----
879 // Emit the call site parameter's value as an entry value. ----
880 if (ShouldTryEmitEntryVals) { 0
881 // Create an expression where the register's entry value is used. ----
882 DIExpression *EntryExpr = DIExpression::get( 0
883 MF->getFunction().getContext(), {dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_entry_value, 1}); 0
884 for (auto &RegEntry : ForwardedRegWorklist) { 0
885 MachineLocation MLoc(RegEntry.first); 0
886 finishCallSiteParams(MLoc, EntryExpr, RegEntry.second, Params); 0
887 } ----
888 } ----
889 } 0
890 ----
891 void DwarfDebug::constructCallSiteEntryDIEs(const DISubprogram &SP, 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
892 DwarfCompileUnit &CU, DIE &ScopeDIE, ----
893 const MachineFunction &MF) { ----
894 // Add a call site-related attribute (DWARF5, Sec. 3.3.1.3). Do this only if ----
895 // the subprogram is required to have one. ----
896 if (!SP.areAllCallsDescribed() || !SP.isDefinition()) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
897 return; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
898 ----
899 // Use DW_AT_call_all_calls to express that call site entries are present ----
900 // for both tail and non-tail calls. Don't use DW_AT_call_all_source_calls ----
901 // because one of its requirements is not met: call site entries for ----
902 // optimized-out calls are elided. ----
903 CU.addFlag(ScopeDIE, CU.getDwarf5OrGNUAttr(dwarf::DW_AT_call_all_calls)); 0
904 ----
905 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = MF.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
906 assert(TII && "TargetInstrInfo not found: cannot label tail calls"); 0
907 ----
908 // Delay slot support check. ----
909 auto delaySlotSupported = [&](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
910 if (!MI.isBundledWithSucc()) 0
911 return false; 0
912 auto Suc = std::next(MI.getIterator()); 0
913 auto CallInstrBundle = getBundleStart(MI.getIterator()); 0
914 (void)CallInstrBundle; ----
915 auto DelaySlotBundle = getBundleStart(Suc); 0
916 (void)DelaySlotBundle; ----
917 // Ensure that label after call is following delay slot instruction. ----
918 // Ex. CALL_INSTRUCTION { ----
919 // DELAY_SLOT_INSTRUCTION } ----
920 // LABEL_AFTER_CALL ----
921 assert(getLabelAfterInsn(&*CallInstrBundle) == 0
922 getLabelAfterInsn(&*DelaySlotBundle) && ----
923 "Call and its successor instruction don't have same label after."); ----
924 return true; 0
925 }; 0
926 ----
927 // Emit call site entries for each call or tail call in the function. ----
928 for (const MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) { 0
929 for (const MachineInstr &MI : MBB.instrs()) { 0
930 // Bundles with call in them will pass the isCall() test below but do not ----
931 // have callee operand information so skip them here. Iterator will ----
932 // eventually reach the call MI. ----
933 if (MI.isBundle()) 0
934 continue; 0
935 ----
936 // Skip instructions which aren't calls. Both calls and tail-calling jump ----
937 // instructions (e.g TAILJMPd64) are classified correctly here. ----
938 if (!MI.isCandidateForCallSiteEntry()) 0
939 continue; 0
940 ----
941 // Skip instructions marked as frame setup, as they are not interesting to ----
942 // the user. ----
943 if (MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::FrameSetup)) 0
944 continue; 0
945 ----
946 // Check if delay slot support is enabled. ----
947 if (MI.hasDelaySlot() && !delaySlotSupported(*&MI)) 0
948 return; 0
949 ----
950 // If this is a direct call, find the callee's subprogram. ----
951 // In the case of an indirect call find the register that holds ----
952 // the callee. ----
953 const MachineOperand &CalleeOp = TII->getCalleeOperand(MI); 0
954 if (!CalleeOp.isGlobal() && 0
955 (!CalleeOp.isReg() || !CalleeOp.getReg().isPhysical())) 0
956 continue; 0
957 ----
958 unsigned CallReg = 0; 0
959 const DISubprogram *CalleeSP = nullptr; 0
960 const Function *CalleeDecl = nullptr; 0
961 if (CalleeOp.isReg()) { 0
962 CallReg = CalleeOp.getReg(); 0
963 if (!CallReg) 0
964 continue; 0
965 } else { ----
966 CalleeDecl = dyn_cast(CalleeOp.getGlobal()); 0
967 if (!CalleeDecl || !CalleeDecl->getSubprogram()) 0
968 continue; 0
969 CalleeSP = CalleeDecl->getSubprogram(); 0
970 } ----
971 ----
972 // TODO: Omit call site entries for runtime calls (objc_msgSend, etc). ----
973 ----
974 bool IsTail = TII->isTailCall(MI); 0
975 ----
976 // If MI is in a bundle, the label was created after the bundle since ----
977 // EmitFunctionBody iterates over top-level MIs. Get that top-level MI ----
978 // to search for that label below. ----
979 const MachineInstr *TopLevelCallMI = ----
980 MI.isInsideBundle() ? &*getBundleStart(MI.getIterator()) : &MI; 0
981 ----
982 // For non-tail calls, the return PC is needed to disambiguate paths in ----
983 // the call graph which could lead to some target function. For tail ----
984 // calls, no return PC information is needed, unless tuning for GDB in ----
985 // DWARF4 mode in which case we fake a return PC for compatibility. ----
986 const MCSymbol *PCAddr = ----
987 (!IsTail || CU.useGNUAnalogForDwarf5Feature()) 0
988 ? const_cast(getLabelAfterInsn(TopLevelCallMI)) 0
989 : nullptr; 0
990 ----
991 // For tail calls, it's necessary to record the address of the branch ----
992 // instruction so that the debugger can show where the tail call occurred. ----
993 const MCSymbol *CallAddr = ----
994 IsTail ? getLabelBeforeInsn(TopLevelCallMI) : nullptr; 0
995 ----
996 assert((IsTail || PCAddr) && "Non-tail call without return PC"); 0
997 ----
998 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CallSiteEntry: " << MF.getName() << " -> " 0
999 << (CalleeDecl ? CalleeDecl->getName() ----
1000 : StringRef(MF.getSubtarget() ----
1001 .getRegisterInfo() ----
1002 ->getName(CallReg))) ----
1003 << (IsTail ? " [IsTail]" : "") << "\n"); ----
1004 ----
1005 DIE &CallSiteDIE = CU.constructCallSiteEntryDIE( 0
1006 ScopeDIE, CalleeSP, IsTail, PCAddr, CallAddr, CallReg); ----
1007 ----
1008 // Optionally emit call-site-param debug info. ----
1009 if (emitDebugEntryValues()) { 0
1010 ParamSet Params; 0
1011 // Try to interpret values of call site parameters. ----
1012 collectCallSiteParameters(&MI, Params); 0
1013 CU.constructCallSiteParmEntryDIEs(CallSiteDIE, Params); 0
1014 } 0
1015 } ----
1016 } ----
1017 } ----

1020 if (!U.hasDwarfPubSections()) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1021 return; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1022 ----
1023 U.addFlag(D, dwarf::DW_AT_GNU_pubnames); 0

1026 void DwarfDebug::finishUnitAttributes(const DICompileUnit *DIUnit, 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1027 DwarfCompileUnit &NewCU) { ----
1028 DIE &Die = NewCU.getUnitDie(); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1029 StringRef FN = DIUnit->getFilename(); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1030 ----
1031 StringRef Producer = DIUnit->getProducer(); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1032 StringRef Flags = DIUnit->getFlags(); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1033 if (!Flags.empty() && !useAppleExtensionAttributes()) { 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1034 std::string ProducerWithFlags = Producer.str() + " " + Flags.str(); 0
1035 NewCU.addString(Die, dwarf::DW_AT_producer, ProducerWithFlags); 0
1036 } else 0
1037 NewCU.addString(Die, dwarf::DW_AT_producer, Producer); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1038 ----
1039 NewCU.addUInt(Die, dwarf::DW_AT_language, dwarf::DW_FORM_data2, 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1040 DIUnit->getSourceLanguage()); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1041 NewCU.addString(Die, dwarf::DW_AT_name, FN); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1042 StringRef SysRoot = DIUnit->getSysRoot(); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1043 if (!SysRoot.empty()) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1044 NewCU.addString(Die, dwarf::DW_AT_LLVM_sysroot, SysRoot); 0
1045 StringRef SDK = DIUnit->getSDK(); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1046 if (!SDK.empty()) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1047 NewCU.addString(Die, dwarf::DW_AT_APPLE_sdk, SDK); 0
1048 ----
1049 if (!useSplitDwarf()) { 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1050 // Add DW_str_offsets_base to the unit DIE, except for split units. ----
1051 if (useSegmentedStringOffsetsTable()) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1052 NewCU.addStringOffsetsStart(); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1053 ----
1054 NewCU.initStmtList(); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll

1132 /// Sort and unique GVEs by comparing their fragment offset. ----
1133 static SmallVectorImpl & ----
1134 sortGlobalExprs(SmallVectorImpl &GVEs) { 0
1135 llvm::sort( 0
1136 GVEs, [](DwarfCompileUnit::GlobalExpr A, DwarfCompileUnit::GlobalExpr B) { 0
1137 // Sort order: first null exprs, then exprs without fragment ----
1138 // info, then sort by fragment offset in bits. ----
1139 // FIXME: Come up with a more comprehensive comparator so ----
1140 // the sorting isn't non-deterministic, and so the following ----
1141 // std::unique call works correctly. ----
1142 if (!A.Expr || !B.Expr) 0
1143 return !!B.Expr; 0
1144 auto FragmentA = A.Expr->getFragmentInfo(); 0
1145 auto FragmentB = B.Expr->getFragmentInfo(); 0
1146 if (!FragmentA || !FragmentB) 0
1147 return !!FragmentB; 0
1148 return FragmentA->OffsetInBits < FragmentB->OffsetInBits; 0
1149 }); ----
1150 GVEs.erase(std::unique(GVEs.begin(), GVEs.end(), 0
1151 [](DwarfCompileUnit::GlobalExpr A, 0
1152 DwarfCompileUnit::GlobalExpr B) { ----
1153 return A.Expr == B.Expr; 0
1154 }), ----
1155 GVEs.end()); 0
1156 return GVEs; 0
1157 } ----

1589 /// Determine whether a *singular* DBG_VALUE is valid for the entirety of its ----
1590 /// enclosing lexical scope. The check ensures there are no other instructions ----
1591 /// in the same lexical scope preceding the DBG_VALUE and that its range is ----
1592 /// either open or otherwise rolls off the end of the scope. ----
1593 static bool validThroughout(LexicalScopes &LScopes, 0
1594 const MachineInstr *DbgValue, ----
1595 const MachineInstr *RangeEnd, ----
1596 const InstructionOrdering &Ordering) { ----
1597 assert(DbgValue->getDebugLoc() && "DBG_VALUE without a debug location"); 0
1598 auto MBB = DbgValue->getParent(); 0
1599 auto DL = DbgValue->getDebugLoc(); 0
1600 auto *LScope = LScopes.findLexicalScope(DL); 0
1601 // Scope doesn't exist; this is a dead DBG_VALUE. ----
1602 if (!LScope) 0
1603 return false; 0
1604 auto &LSRange = LScope->getRanges(); 0
1605 if (LSRange.size() == 0) 0
1606 return false; 0
1607 ----
1608 const MachineInstr *LScopeBegin = LSRange.front().first; 0
1609 // If the scope starts before the DBG_VALUE then we may have a negative ----
1610 // result. Otherwise the location is live coming into the scope and we ----
1611 // can skip the following checks. ----
1612 if (!Ordering.isBefore(DbgValue, LScopeBegin)) { 0
1613 // Exit if the lexical scope begins outside of the current block. ----
1614 if (LScopeBegin->getParent() != MBB) 0
1615 return false; 0
1616 ----
1617 MachineBasicBlock::const_reverse_iterator Pred(DbgValue); 0
1618 for (++Pred; Pred != MBB->rend(); ++Pred) { 0
1619 if (Pred->getFlag(MachineInstr::FrameSetup)) 0
1620 break; 0
1621 auto PredDL = Pred->getDebugLoc(); 0
1622 if (!PredDL || Pred->isMetaInstruction()) 0
1623 continue; 0
1624 // Check whether the instruction preceding the DBG_VALUE is in the same ----
1625 // (sub)scope as the DBG_VALUE. ----
1626 if (DL->getScope() == PredDL->getScope()) 0
1627 return false; 0
1628 auto *PredScope = LScopes.findLexicalScope(PredDL); 0
1629 if (!PredScope || LScope->dominates(PredScope)) 0
1630 return false; 0
1631 } 0
1632 } ----
1633 ----
1634 // If the range of the DBG_VALUE is open-ended, report success. ----
1635 if (!RangeEnd) 0
1636 return true; 0
1637 ----
1638 // Single, constant DBG_VALUEs in the prologue are promoted to be live ----
1639 // throughout the function. This is a hack, presumably for DWARF v2 and not ----
1640 // necessarily correct. It would be much better to use a dbg.declare instead ----
1641 // if we know the constant is live throughout the scope. ----
1642 if (MBB->pred_empty() && 0
1643 all_of(DbgValue->debug_operands(), 0
1644 [](const MachineOperand &Op) { return Op.isImm(); })) 0
1645 return true; 0
1646 ----
1647 // Test if the location terminates before the end of the scope. ----
1648 const MachineInstr *LScopeEnd = LSRange.back().second; 0
1649 if (Ordering.isBefore(RangeEnd, LScopeEnd)) 0
1650 return false; 0
1651 ----
1652 // There's a single location which starts at the scope start, and ends at or ----
1653 // after the scope end. ----
1654 return true; 0
1655 } 0
1656 ----
1657 /// Build the location list for all DBG_VALUEs in the function that ----
1658 /// describe the same variable. The resulting DebugLocEntries will have ----
1659 /// strict monotonically increasing begin addresses and will never ----
1660 /// overlap. If the resulting list has only one entry that is valid ----
1661 /// throughout variable's scope return true. ----
1662 // ----
1663 // See the definition of DbgValueHistoryMap::Entry for an explanation of the ----
1664 // different kinds of history map entries. One thing to be aware of is that if ----
1665 // a debug value is ended by another entry (rather than being valid until the ----
1666 // end of the function), that entry's instruction may or may not be included in ----
1667 // the range, depending on if the entry is a clobbering entry (it has an ----
1668 // instruction that clobbers one or more preceding locations), or if it is an ----
1669 // (overlapping) debug value entry. This distinction can be seen in the example ----
1670 // below. The first debug value is ended by the clobbering entry 2, and the ----
1671 // second and third debug values are ended by the overlapping debug value entry ----
1672 // 4. ----
1673 // ----
1674 // Input: ----
1675 // ----
1676 // History map entries [type, end index, mi] ----
1677 // ----
1678 // 0 | [DbgValue, 2, DBG_VALUE $reg0, [...] (fragment 0, 32)] ----
1679 // 1 | | [DbgValue, 4, DBG_VALUE $reg1, [...] (fragment 32, 32)] ----
1680 // 2 | | [Clobber, $reg0 = [...], -, -] ----
1681 // 3 | | [DbgValue, 4, DBG_VALUE 123, [...] (fragment 64, 32)] ----
1682 // 4 [DbgValue, ~0, DBG_VALUE @g, [...] (fragment 0, 96)] ----
1683 // ----
1684 // Output [start, end) [Value...]: ----
1685 // ----
1686 // [0-1) [(reg0, fragment 0, 32)] ----
1687 // [1-3) [(reg0, fragment 0, 32), (reg1, fragment 32, 32)] ----
1688 // [3-4) [(reg1, fragment 32, 32), (123, fragment 64, 32)] ----
1689 // [4-) [(@g, fragment 0, 96)] ----
1690 bool DwarfDebug::buildLocationList(SmallVectorImpl &DebugLoc, 0
1691 const DbgValueHistoryMap::Entries &Entries) { ----
1692 using OpenRange = ----
1693 std::pair; ----
1694 SmallVector OpenRanges; 0
1695 bool isSafeForSingleLocation = true; 0
1696 const MachineInstr *StartDebugMI = nullptr; 0
1697 const MachineInstr *EndMI = nullptr; 0
1698 ----
1699 for (auto EB = Entries.begin(), EI = EB, EE = Entries.end(); EI != EE; ++EI) { 0
1700 const MachineInstr *Instr = EI->getInstr(); 0
1701 ----
1702 // Remove all values that are no longer live. ----
1703 size_t Index = std::distance(EB, EI); 0
1704 erase_if(OpenRanges, [&](OpenRange &R) { return R.first <= Index; }); 0
1705 ----
1706 // If we are dealing with a clobbering entry, this iteration will result in ----
1707 // a location list entry starting after the clobbering instruction. ----
1708 const MCSymbol *StartLabel = ----
1709 EI->isClobber() ? getLabelAfterInsn(Instr) : getLabelBeforeInsn(Instr); 0
1710 assert(StartLabel && 0
1711 "Forgot label before/after instruction starting a range!"); ----
1712 ----
1713 const MCSymbol *EndLabel; ----
1714 if (std::next(EI) == Entries.end()) { 0
1715 const MachineBasicBlock &EndMBB = Asm->MF->back(); 0
1716 EndLabel = Asm->MBBSectionRanges[EndMBB.getSectionIDNum()].EndLabel; 0
1717 if (EI->isClobber()) 0
1718 EndMI = EI->getInstr(); 0
1719 } ----
1720 else if (std::next(EI)->isClobber()) 0
1721 EndLabel = getLabelAfterInsn(std::next(EI)->getInstr()); 0
1722 else ----
1723 EndLabel = getLabelBeforeInsn(std::next(EI)->getInstr()); 0
1724 assert(EndLabel && "Forgot label after instruction ending a range!"); 0
1725 ----
1726 if (EI->isDbgValue()) 0
1727 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "DotDebugLoc: " << *Instr << "\n"); 0
1728 ----
1729 // If this history map entry has a debug value, add that to the list of ----
1730 // open ranges and check if its location is valid for a single value ----
1731 // location. ----
1732 if (EI->isDbgValue()) { 0
1733 // Do not add undef debug values, as they are redundant information in ----
1734 // the location list entries. An undef debug results in an empty location ----
1735 // description. If there are any non-undef fragments then padding pieces ----
1736 // with empty location descriptions will automatically be inserted, and if ----
1737 // all fragments are undef then the whole location list entry is ----
1738 // redundant. ----
1739 if (!Instr->isUndefDebugValue()) { 0
1740 auto Value = getDebugLocValue(Instr); 0
1741 OpenRanges.emplace_back(EI->getEndIndex(), Value); 0
1742 ----
1743 // TODO: Add support for single value fragment locations. ----
1744 if (Instr->getDebugExpression()->isFragment()) 0
1745 isSafeForSingleLocation = false; 0
1746 ----
1747 if (!StartDebugMI) 0
1748 StartDebugMI = Instr; 0
1749 } else { 0
1750 isSafeForSingleLocation = false; 0
1751 } ----
1752 } ----
1753 ----
1754 // Location list entries with empty location descriptions are redundant ----
1755 // information in DWARF, so do not emit those. ----
1756 if (OpenRanges.empty()) 0
1757 continue; 0
1758 ----
1759 // Omit entries with empty ranges as they do not have any effect in DWARF. ----
1760 if (StartLabel == EndLabel) { 0
1761 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Omitting location list entry with empty range.\n"); 0
1762 continue; 0
1763 } ----
1764 ----
1765 SmallVector Values; 0
1766 for (auto &R : OpenRanges) 0
1767 Values.push_back(R.second); 0
1768 ----
1769 // With Basic block sections, it is posssible that the StartLabel and the ----
1770 // Instr are not in the same section. This happens when the StartLabel is ----
1771 // the function begin label and the dbg value appears in a basic block ----
1772 // that is not the entry. In this case, the range needs to be split to ----
1773 // span each individual section in the range from StartLabel to EndLabel. ----
1774 if (Asm->MF->hasBBSections() && StartLabel == Asm->getFunctionBegin() && 0
1775 !Instr->getParent()->sameSection(&Asm->MF->front())) { 0
1776 const MCSymbol *BeginSectionLabel = StartLabel; 0
1777 ----
1778 for (const MachineBasicBlock &MBB : *Asm->MF) { 0
1779 if (MBB.isBeginSection() && &MBB != &Asm->MF->front()) 0
1780 BeginSectionLabel = MBB.getSymbol(); 0
1781 ----
1782 if (MBB.sameSection(Instr->getParent())) { 0
1783 DebugLoc.emplace_back(BeginSectionLabel, EndLabel, Values); 0
1784 break; 0
1785 } ----
1786 if (MBB.isEndSection()) 0
1787 DebugLoc.emplace_back(BeginSectionLabel, MBB.getEndSymbol(), Values); 0
1788 } ----
1789 } else { ----
1790 DebugLoc.emplace_back(StartLabel, EndLabel, Values); 0
1791 } ----
1792 ----
1793 // Attempt to coalesce the ranges of two otherwise identical ----
1794 // DebugLocEntries. ----
1795 auto CurEntry = DebugLoc.rbegin(); 0
1796 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
1797 dbgs() << CurEntry->getValues().size() << " Values:\n"; ----
1798 for (auto &Value : CurEntry->getValues()) ----
1799 Value.dump(); ----
1800 dbgs() << "-----\n"; ----
1801 }); ----
1802 ----
1803 auto PrevEntry = std::next(CurEntry); 0
1804 if (PrevEntry != DebugLoc.rend() && PrevEntry->MergeRanges(*CurEntry)) 0
1805 DebugLoc.pop_back(); 0
1806 } 0
1807 ----
1808 if (!isSafeForSingleLocation || 0
1809 !validThroughout(LScopes, StartDebugMI, EndMI, getInstOrdering())) 0
1810 return false; 0
1811 ----
1812 if (DebugLoc.size() == 1) 0
1813 return true; 0
1814 ----
1815 if (!Asm->MF->hasBBSections()) 0
1816 return false; 0
1817 ----
1818 // Check here to see if loclist can be merged into a single range. If not, ----
1819 // we must keep the split loclists per section. This does exactly what ----
1820 // MergeRanges does without sections. We don't actually merge the ranges ----
1821 // as the split ranges must be kept intact if this cannot be collapsed ----
1822 // into a single range. ----
1823 const MachineBasicBlock *RangeMBB = nullptr; 0
1824 if (DebugLoc[0].getBeginSym() == Asm->getFunctionBegin()) 0
1825 RangeMBB = &Asm->MF->front(); 0
1826 else ----
1827 RangeMBB = Entries.begin()->getInstr()->getParent(); 0
1828 auto *CurEntry = DebugLoc.begin(); 0
1829 auto *NextEntry = std::next(CurEntry); 0
1830 while (NextEntry != DebugLoc.end()) { 0
1831 // Get the last machine basic block of this section. ----
1832 while (!RangeMBB->isEndSection()) 0
1833 RangeMBB = RangeMBB->getNextNode(); 0
1834 if (!RangeMBB->getNextNode()) 0
1835 return false; 0
1836 // CurEntry should end the current section and NextEntry should start ----
1837 // the next section and the Values must match for these two ranges to be ----
1838 // merged. ----
1839 if (CurEntry->getEndSym() != RangeMBB->getEndSymbol() || 0
1840 NextEntry->getBeginSym() != RangeMBB->getNextNode()->getSymbol() || 0
1841 CurEntry->getValues() != NextEntry->getValues()) 0
1842 return false; 0
1843 RangeMBB = RangeMBB->getNextNode(); 0
1844 CurEntry = NextEntry; 0
1845 NextEntry = std::next(CurEntry); 0
1846 } ----
1847 return true; 0
1848 } 0

1999 // Process beginning of an instruction. ----
2000 void DwarfDebug::beginInstruction(const MachineInstr *MI) { 23 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
2001 const MachineFunction &MF = *MI->getMF(); 23 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
2002 const auto *SP = MF.getFunction().getSubprogram(); 23 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
2003 bool NoDebug = ----
2004 !SP || SP->getUnit()->getEmissionKind() == DICompileUnit::NoDebug; 23 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
2005 ----
2006 // Delay slot support check. ----
2007 auto delaySlotSupported = [](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2008 if (!MI.isBundledWithSucc()) 0
2009 return false; 0
2010 auto Suc = std::next(MI.getIterator()); 0
2011 (void)Suc; ----
2012 // Ensure that delay slot instruction is successor of the call instruction. ----
2013 // Ex. CALL_INSTRUCTION { ----
2014 // DELAY_SLOT_INSTRUCTION } ----
2015 assert(Suc->isBundledWithPred() && 0
2016 "Call bundle instructions are out of order"); ----
2017 return true; 0
2018 }; ----
2019 ----
2020 // When describing calls, we need a label for the call instruction. ----
2021 if (!NoDebug && SP->areAllCallsDescribed() && 23 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
2022 MI->isCandidateForCallSiteEntry(MachineInstr::AnyInBundle) && 46 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
2023 (!MI->hasDelaySlot() || delaySlotSupported(*MI))) { 0
2024 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = MF.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
2025 bool IsTail = TII->isTailCall(*MI); 0
2026 // For tail calls, we need the address of the branch instruction for ----
2027 // DW_AT_call_pc. ----
2028 if (IsTail) 0
2029 requestLabelBeforeInsn(MI); 0
2030 // For non-tail calls, we need the return address for the call for ----

2432 ----
2433 // Public name handling. ----
2434 // The format for the various pubnames: ----
2435 // ----
2436 // dwarf pubnames - offset/name pairs where the offset is the offset into the CU ----
2437 // for the DIE that is named. ----
2438 // ----
2439 // gnu pubnames - offset/index value/name tuples where the offset is the offset ----
2440 // into the CU and the index value is computed according to the type of value ----
2441 // for the DIE that is named. ----
2442 // ----
2443 // For type units the offset is the offset of the skeleton DIE. For split dwarf ----
2444 // it's the offset within the debug_info/debug_types dwo section, however, the ----
2445 // reference in the pubname header doesn't change. ----
2446 ----
2447 /// computeIndexValue - Compute the gdb index value for the DIE and CU. ----
2448 static dwarf::PubIndexEntryDescriptor computeIndexValue(DwarfUnit *CU, 0
2449 const DIE *Die) { ----
2450 // Entities that ended up only in a Type Unit reference the CU instead (since ----
2451 // the pub entry has offsets within the CU there's no real offset that can be ----
2452 // provided anyway). As it happens all such entities (namespaces and types, ----
2453 // types only in C++ at that) are rendered as TYPE+EXTERNAL. If this turns out ----
2454 // not to be true it would be necessary to persist this information from the ----
2455 // point at which the entry is added to the index data structure - since by ----
2456 // the time the index is built from that, the original type/namespace DIE in a ----
2457 // type unit has already been destroyed so it can't be queried for properties ----
2458 // like tag, etc. ----
2459 if (Die->getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_compile_unit) 0
2460 return dwarf::PubIndexEntryDescriptor(dwarf::GIEK_TYPE, 0
2461 dwarf::GIEL_EXTERNAL); 0
2462 dwarf::GDBIndexEntryLinkage Linkage = dwarf::GIEL_STATIC; 0
2463 ----
2464 // We could have a specification DIE that has our most of our knowledge, ----
2465 // look for that now. ----
2466 if (DIEValue SpecVal = Die->findAttribute(dwarf::DW_AT_specification)) { 0
2467 DIE &SpecDIE = SpecVal.getDIEEntry().getEntry(); 0
2468 if (SpecDIE.findAttribute(dwarf::DW_AT_external)) 0
2469 Linkage = dwarf::GIEL_EXTERNAL; 0
2470 } else if (Die->findAttribute(dwarf::DW_AT_external)) 0
2471 Linkage = dwarf::GIEL_EXTERNAL; 0
2472 ----
2473 switch (Die->getTag()) { 0
2474 case dwarf::DW_TAG_class_type: 0
2475 case dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type: ----
2476 case dwarf::DW_TAG_union_type: ----
2477 case dwarf::DW_TAG_enumeration_type: ----
2478 return dwarf::PubIndexEntryDescriptor( 0
2479 dwarf::GIEK_TYPE, ----
2480 dwarf::isCPlusPlus((dwarf::SourceLanguage)CU->getLanguage()) 0
2481 ? dwarf::GIEL_EXTERNAL ----
2482 : dwarf::GIEL_STATIC); 0
2483 case dwarf::DW_TAG_typedef: 0
2484 case dwarf::DW_TAG_base_type: ----
2485 case dwarf::DW_TAG_subrange_type: ----
2486 return dwarf::PubIndexEntryDescriptor(dwarf::GIEK_TYPE, dwarf::GIEL_STATIC); 0
2487 case dwarf::DW_TAG_namespace: 0
2488 return dwarf::GIEK_TYPE; 0
2489 case dwarf::DW_TAG_subprogram: 0
2490 return dwarf::PubIndexEntryDescriptor(dwarf::GIEK_FUNCTION, Linkage); 0
2491 case dwarf::DW_TAG_variable: 0
2492 return dwarf::PubIndexEntryDescriptor(dwarf::GIEK_VARIABLE, Linkage); 0
2493 case dwarf::DW_TAG_enumerator: 0
2494 return dwarf::PubIndexEntryDescriptor(dwarf::GIEK_VARIABLE, 0
2495 dwarf::GIEL_STATIC); 0
2496 default: 0
2497 return dwarf::GIEK_NONE; 0
2498 } ----
2499 } ----

2531 ----
2532 void DwarfDebug::emitDebugPubSection(bool GnuStyle, StringRef Name, 0
2533 DwarfCompileUnit *TheU, ----
2534 const StringMap &Globals) { ----
2535 if (auto *Skeleton = TheU->getSkeleton()) 0
2536 TheU = Skeleton; 0
2537 ----
2538 // Emit the header. ----
2539 MCSymbol *EndLabel = Asm->emitDwarfUnitLength( 0
2540 "pub" + Name, "Length of Public " + Name + " Info"); 0
2541 ----
2542 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("DWARF Version"); 0
2543 Asm->emitInt16(dwarf::DW_PUBNAMES_VERSION); 0
2544 ----
2545 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("Offset of Compilation Unit Info"); 0
2546 emitSectionReference(*TheU); 0
2547 ----
2548 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("Compilation Unit Length"); 0
2549 Asm->emitDwarfLengthOrOffset(TheU->getLength()); 0
2550 ----
2551 // Emit the pubnames for this compilation unit. ----
2552 SmallVector, 0> Vec; 0
2553 for (const auto &GI : Globals) 0
2554 Vec.emplace_back(GI.first(), GI.second); 0
2555 llvm::sort(Vec, [](auto &A, auto &B) { 0
2556 return A.second->getOffset() < B.second->getOffset(); 0
2557 }); ----
2558 for (const auto &[Name, Entity] : Vec) { 0
2559 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("DIE offset"); 0
2560 Asm->emitDwarfLengthOrOffset(Entity->getOffset()); 0
2561 ----
2562 if (GnuStyle) { 0
2563 dwarf::PubIndexEntryDescriptor Desc = computeIndexValue(TheU, Entity); 0
2564 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment( 0
2565 Twine("Attributes: ") + dwarf::GDBIndexEntryKindString(Desc.Kind) + 0
2566 ", " + dwarf::GDBIndexEntryLinkageString(Desc.Linkage)); 0
2567 Asm->emitInt8(Desc.toBits()); 0
2568 } ----
2569 ----
2570 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("External Name"); 0
2571 Asm->OutStreamer->emitBytes(StringRef(Name.data(), Name.size() + 1)); 0
2572 } ----
2573 ----
2574 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("End Mark"); 0
2575 Asm->emitDwarfLengthOrOffset(0); 0
2576 Asm->OutStreamer->emitLabel(EndLabel); 0
2577 } 0

2590 ----
2591 void DwarfDebug::emitDebugLocEntry(ByteStreamer &Streamer, 0
2592 const DebugLocStream::Entry &Entry, ----
2593 const DwarfCompileUnit *CU) { ----
2594 auto &&Comments = DebugLocs.getComments(Entry); 0
2595 auto Comment = Comments.begin(); 0
2596 auto End = Comments.end(); 0
2597 ----
2598 // The expressions are inserted into a byte stream rather early (see ----
2599 // DwarfExpression::addExpression) so for those ops (e.g. DW_OP_convert) that ----
2600 // need to reference a base_type DIE the offset of that DIE is not yet known. ----
2601 // To deal with this we instead insert a placeholder early and then extract ----
2602 // it here and replace it with the real reference. ----
2603 unsigned PtrSize = Asm->MAI->getCodePointerSize(); 0
2604 DWARFDataExtractor Data(StringRef(DebugLocs.getBytes(Entry).data(), 0
2605 DebugLocs.getBytes(Entry).size()), 0
2606 Asm->getDataLayout().isLittleEndian(), PtrSize); 0
2607 DWARFExpression Expr(Data, PtrSize, Asm->OutContext.getDwarfFormat()); 0
2608 ----
2609 using Encoding = DWARFExpression::Operation::Encoding; ----
2610 uint64_t Offset = 0; 0
2611 for (const auto &Op : Expr) { 0
2612 assert(Op.getCode() != dwarf::DW_OP_const_type && 0
2613 "3 operand ops not yet supported"); ----
2614 assert(!Op.getSubCode() && "SubOps not yet supported"); 0
2615 Streamer.emitInt8(Op.getCode(), Comment != End ? *(Comment++) : ""); 0
2616 Offset++; 0
2617 for (unsigned I = 0; I < Op.getDescription().Op.size(); ++I) { 0
2618 if (Op.getDescription().Op[I] == Encoding::BaseTypeRef) { 0
2619 unsigned Length = ----
2620 Streamer.emitDIERef(*CU->ExprRefedBaseTypes[Op.getRawOperand(I)].Die); 0
2621 // Make sure comments stay aligned. ----
2622 for (unsigned J = 0; J < Length; ++J) 0
2623 if (Comment != End) 0
2624 Comment++; 0
2625 } else { ----
2626 for (uint64_t J = Offset; J < Op.getOperandEndOffset(I); ++J) 0
2627 Streamer.emitInt8(Data.getData()[J], Comment != End ? *(Comment++) : ""); 0
2628 } ----
2629 Offset = Op.getOperandEndOffset(I); 0
2630 } ----
2631 assert(Offset == Op.getEndOffset()); 0
2632 } 0
2633 } 0
2634 ----
2635 void DwarfDebug::emitDebugLocValue(const AsmPrinter &AP, const DIBasicType *BT, 0
2636 const DbgValueLoc &Value, ----
2637 DwarfExpression &DwarfExpr) { ----
2638 auto *DIExpr = Value.getExpression(); 0
2639 DIExpressionCursor ExprCursor(DIExpr); 0
2640 DwarfExpr.addFragmentOffset(DIExpr); 0
2641 ----
2642 // If the DIExpr is is an Entry Value, we want to follow the same code path ----
2643 // regardless of whether the DBG_VALUE is variadic or not. ----
2644 if (DIExpr && DIExpr->isEntryValue()) { 0
2645 // Entry values can only be a single register with no additional DIExpr, ----
2646 // so just add it directly. ----
2647 assert(Value.getLocEntries().size() == 1); 0
2648 assert(Value.getLocEntries()[0].isLocation()); 0
2649 MachineLocation Location = Value.getLocEntries()[0].getLoc(); 0
2650 DwarfExpr.setLocation(Location, DIExpr); 0
2651 ----
2652 DwarfExpr.beginEntryValueExpression(ExprCursor); 0
2653 ----
2654 const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI = *AP.MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
2655 if (!DwarfExpr.addMachineRegExpression(TRI, ExprCursor, Location.getReg())) 0
2656 return; 0
2657 return DwarfExpr.addExpression(std::move(ExprCursor)); 0
2658 } ----
2659 ----
2660 // Regular entry. ----
2661 auto EmitValueLocEntry = [&DwarfExpr, &BT, 0
2662 &AP](const DbgValueLocEntry &Entry, ----
2663 DIExpressionCursor &Cursor) -> bool { 0
2664 if (Entry.isInt()) { 0
2665 if (BT && (BT->getEncoding() == dwarf::DW_ATE_signed || 0
2666 BT->getEncoding() == dwarf::DW_ATE_signed_char)) 0
2667 DwarfExpr.addSignedConstant(Entry.getInt()); 0
2668 else ----
2669 DwarfExpr.addUnsignedConstant(Entry.getInt()); 0
2670 } else if (Entry.isLocation()) { 0
2671 MachineLocation Location = Entry.getLoc(); 0
2672 if (Location.isIndirect()) 0
2673 DwarfExpr.setMemoryLocationKind(); 0
2674 ----
2675 const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI = *AP.MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
2676 if (!DwarfExpr.addMachineRegExpression(TRI, Cursor, Location.getReg())) 0
2677 return false; 0
2678 } else if (Entry.isTargetIndexLocation()) { 0
2679 TargetIndexLocation Loc = Entry.getTargetIndexLocation(); 0
2680 // TODO TargetIndexLocation is a target-independent. Currently only the ----
2681 // WebAssembly-specific encoding is supported. ----
2682 assert(AP.TM.getTargetTriple().isWasm()); 0
2683 DwarfExpr.addWasmLocation(Loc.Index, static_cast(Loc.Offset)); 0
2684 } else if (Entry.isConstantFP()) { 0
2685 if (AP.getDwarfVersion() >= 4 && !AP.getDwarfDebug()->tuneForSCE() && 0
2686 !Cursor) { 0
2687 DwarfExpr.addConstantFP(Entry.getConstantFP()->getValueAPF(), AP); 0
2688 } else if (Entry.getConstantFP() 0
2689 ->getValueAPF() 0
2690 .bitcastToAPInt() 0
2691 .getBitWidth() <= 64 /*bits*/) { 0
2692 DwarfExpr.addUnsignedConstant( 0
2693 Entry.getConstantFP()->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt()); 0
2694 } else { ----
2695 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
2696 dbgs() << "Skipped DwarfExpression creation for ConstantFP of size" ----
2697 << Entry.getConstantFP() ----
2698 ->getValueAPF() ----
2699 .bitcastToAPInt() ----
2700 .getBitWidth() ----
2701 << " bits\n"); ----
2702 return false; 0
2703 } ----
2704 } ----
2705 return true; 0
2706 }; 0
2707 ----
2708 if (!Value.isVariadic()) { 0
2709 if (!EmitValueLocEntry(Value.getLocEntries()[0], ExprCursor)) 0
2710 return; 0
2711 DwarfExpr.addExpression(std::move(ExprCursor)); 0
2712 return; 0
2713 } ----
2714 ----
2715 // If any of the location entries are registers with the value 0, then the ----
2716 // location is undefined. ----
2717 if (any_of(Value.getLocEntries(), [](const DbgValueLocEntry &Entry) { 0
2718 return Entry.isLocation() && !Entry.getLoc().getReg(); 0
2719 })) ----
2720 return; 0
2721 ----
2722 DwarfExpr.addExpression( 0
2723 std::move(ExprCursor), 0
2724 [EmitValueLocEntry, &Value](unsigned Idx, 0
2725 DIExpressionCursor &Cursor) -> bool { 0
2726 return EmitValueLocEntry(Value.getLocEntries()[Idx], Cursor); 0
2727 }); ----
2728 } ----
2729 ----
2730 void DebugLocEntry::finalize(const AsmPrinter &AP, 0
2731 DebugLocStream::ListBuilder &List, ----
2732 const DIBasicType *BT, ----
2733 DwarfCompileUnit &TheCU) { ----
2734 assert(!Values.empty() && 0
2735 "location list entries without values are redundant"); ----
2736 assert(Begin != End && "unexpected location list entry with empty range"); 0
2737 DebugLocStream::EntryBuilder Entry(List, Begin, End); 0
2738 BufferByteStreamer Streamer = Entry.getStreamer(); 0
2739 DebugLocDwarfExpression DwarfExpr(AP.getDwarfVersion(), Streamer, TheCU); 0
2740 const DbgValueLoc &Value = Values[0]; 0
2741 if (Value.isFragment()) { 0
2742 // Emit all fragments that belong to the same variable and range. ----
2743 assert(llvm::all_of(Values, [](DbgValueLoc P) { 0
2744 return P.isFragment(); ----
2745 }) && "all values are expected to be fragments"); ----
2746 assert(llvm::is_sorted(Values) && "fragments are expected to be sorted"); 0
2747 ----
2748 for (const auto &Fragment : Values) 0
2749 DwarfDebug::emitDebugLocValue(AP, BT, Fragment, DwarfExpr); 0
2750 ----
2751 } else { ----
2752 assert(Values.size() == 1 && "only fragments may have >1 value"); 0
2753 DwarfDebug::emitDebugLocValue(AP, BT, Value, DwarfExpr); 0
2754 } ----
2755 DwarfExpr.finalize(); 0
2756 if (DwarfExpr.TagOffset) 0
2757 List.setTagOffset(*DwarfExpr.TagOffset); 0
2758 } 0
2759 ----
2760 void DwarfDebug::emitDebugLocEntryLocation(const DebugLocStream::Entry &Entry, 0
2761 const DwarfCompileUnit *CU) { ----
2762 // Emit the size. ----
2763 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("Loc expr size"); 0
2764 if (getDwarfVersion() >= 5) 0
2765 Asm->emitULEB128(DebugLocs.getBytes(Entry).size()); 0
2766 else if (DebugLocs.getBytes(Entry).size() <= std::numeric_limits::max()) 0
2767 Asm->emitInt16(DebugLocs.getBytes(Entry).size()); 0
2768 else { ----
2769 // The entry is too big to fit into 16 bit, drop it as there is nothing we ----
2770 // can do. ----
2771 Asm->emitInt16(0); 0
2772 return; 0
2773 } ----
2774 // Emit the entry. ----
2775 APByteStreamer Streamer(*Asm); 0
2776 emitDebugLocEntry(Streamer, Entry, CU); 0
2777 } ----
2778 ----
2779 // Emit the header of a DWARF 5 range list table list table. Returns the symbol ----
2780 // that designates the end of the table for the caller to emit when the table is ----
2781 // complete. ----
2782 static MCSymbol *emitRnglistsTableHeader(AsmPrinter *Asm, 0
2783 const DwarfFile &Holder) { ----
2784 MCSymbol *TableEnd = mcdwarf::emitListsTableHeaderStart(*Asm->OutStreamer); 0
2785 ----
2786 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("Offset entry count"); 0
2787 Asm->emitInt32(Holder.getRangeLists().size()); 0
2788 Asm->OutStreamer->emitLabel(Holder.getRnglistsTableBaseSym()); 0
2789 ----
2790 for (const RangeSpanList &List : Holder.getRangeLists()) 0
2791 Asm->emitLabelDifference(List.Label, Holder.getRnglistsTableBaseSym(), 0
2792 Asm->getDwarfOffsetByteSize()); ----
2793 ----
2794 return TableEnd; 0
2795 } ----
2796 ----
2797 // Emit the header of a DWARF 5 locations list table. Returns the symbol that ----
2798 // designates the end of the table for the caller to emit when the table is ----
2799 // complete. ----
2800 static MCSymbol *emitLoclistsTableHeader(AsmPrinter *Asm, 0
2801 const DwarfDebug &DD) { ----
2802 MCSymbol *TableEnd = mcdwarf::emitListsTableHeaderStart(*Asm->OutStreamer); 0
2803 ----
2804 const auto &DebugLocs = DD.getDebugLocs(); 0
2805 ----
2806 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("Offset entry count"); 0
2807 Asm->emitInt32(DebugLocs.getLists().size()); 0
2808 Asm->OutStreamer->emitLabel(DebugLocs.getSym()); 0
2809 ----
2810 for (const auto &List : DebugLocs.getLists()) 0
2811 Asm->emitLabelDifference(List.Label, DebugLocs.getSym(), 0
2812 Asm->getDwarfOffsetByteSize()); ----
2813 ----
2814 return TableEnd; 0
2815 } ----
2816 ----
2817 template ----
2818 static void emitRangeList( 0
2819 DwarfDebug &DD, AsmPrinter *Asm, MCSymbol *Sym, const Ranges &R, ----
2820 const DwarfCompileUnit &CU, unsigned BaseAddressx, unsigned OffsetPair, ----
2821 unsigned StartxLength, unsigned EndOfList, ----
2822 StringRef (*StringifyEnum)(unsigned), ----
2823 bool ShouldUseBaseAddress, ----
2824 PayloadEmitter EmitPayload) { ----
2825 ----
2826 auto Size = Asm->MAI->getCodePointerSize(); 0
2827 bool UseDwarf5 = DD.getDwarfVersion() >= 5; 0
2828 ----
2829 // Emit our symbol so we can find the beginning of the range. ----
2830 Asm->OutStreamer->emitLabel(Sym); 0
2831 ----
2832 // Gather all the ranges that apply to the same section so they can share ----
2833 // a base address entry. ----
2834 MapVector> SectionRanges; 0
2835 ----
2836 for (const auto &Range : R) 0
2837 SectionRanges[&Range.Begin->getSection()].push_back(&Range); 0
2838 ----
2839 const MCSymbol *CUBase = CU.getBaseAddress(); 0
2840 bool BaseIsSet = false; 0
2841 for (const auto &P : SectionRanges) { 0
2842 auto *Base = CUBase; 0
2843 if (!Base && ShouldUseBaseAddress) { 0
2844 const MCSymbol *Begin = P.second.front()->Begin; 0
2845 const MCSymbol *NewBase = DD.getSectionLabel(&Begin->getSection()); 0
2846 if (!UseDwarf5) { 0
2847 Base = NewBase; 0
2848 BaseIsSet = true; 0
2849 Asm->OutStreamer->emitIntValue(-1, Size); 0
2850 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment(" base address"); 0
2851 Asm->OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(Base, Size); 0
2852 } else if (NewBase != Begin || P.second.size() > 1) { 0
2853 // Only use a base address if ----
2854 // * the existing pool address doesn't match (NewBase != Begin) ----
2855 // * or, there's more than one entry to share the base address ----
2856 Base = NewBase; 0
2857 BaseIsSet = true; 0
2858 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment(StringifyEnum(BaseAddressx)); 0
2859 Asm->emitInt8(BaseAddressx); 0
2860 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment(" base address index"); 0
2861 Asm->emitULEB128(DD.getAddressPool().getIndex(Base)); 0
2862 } ----
2863 } else if (BaseIsSet && !UseDwarf5) { 0
2864 BaseIsSet = false; 0
2865 assert(!Base); 0
2866 Asm->OutStreamer->emitIntValue(-1, Size); 0
2867 Asm->OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, Size); 0
2868 } ----
2869 ----
2870 for (const auto *RS : P.second) { 0
2871 const MCSymbol *Begin = RS->Begin; 0
2872 const MCSymbol *End = RS->End; 0
2873 assert(Begin && "Range without a begin symbol?"); 0
2874 assert(End && "Range without an end symbol?"); 0
2875 if (Base) { 0
2876 if (UseDwarf5) { 0
2877 // Emit offset_pair when we have a base. ----
2878 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment(StringifyEnum(OffsetPair)); 0
2879 Asm->emitInt8(OffsetPair); 0
2880 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment(" starting offset"); 0
2881 Asm->emitLabelDifferenceAsULEB128(Begin, Base); 0
2882 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment(" ending offset"); 0
2883 Asm->emitLabelDifferenceAsULEB128(End, Base); 0
2884 } else { ----
2885 Asm->emitLabelDifference(Begin, Base, Size); 0
2886 Asm->emitLabelDifference(End, Base, Size); 0
2887 } ----
2888 } else if (UseDwarf5) { 0
2889 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment(StringifyEnum(StartxLength)); 0
2890 Asm->emitInt8(StartxLength); 0
2891 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment(" start index"); 0
2892 Asm->emitULEB128(DD.getAddressPool().getIndex(Begin)); 0
2893 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment(" length"); 0
2894 Asm->emitLabelDifferenceAsULEB128(End, Begin); 0
2895 } else { ----
2896 Asm->OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(Begin, Size); 0
2897 Asm->OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(End, Size); 0
2898 } ----
2899 EmitPayload(*RS); 0
2900 } ----
2901 } ----
2902 ----
2903 if (UseDwarf5) { 0
2904 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment(StringifyEnum(EndOfList)); 0
2905 Asm->emitInt8(EndOfList); 0
2906 } else { ----
2907 // Terminate the list with two 0 values. ----
2908 Asm->OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, Size); 0
2909 Asm->OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, Size); 0
2910 } ----
2911 } 0
2912 ----
2913 // Handles emission of both debug_loclist / debug_loclist.dwo ----
2914 static void emitLocList(DwarfDebug &DD, AsmPrinter *Asm, const DebugLocStream::List &List) { 0
2915 emitRangeList(DD, Asm, List.Label, DD.getDebugLocs().getEntries(List), 0
2916 *List.CU, dwarf::DW_LLE_base_addressx, 0
2917 dwarf::DW_LLE_offset_pair, dwarf::DW_LLE_startx_length, ----
2918 dwarf::DW_LLE_end_of_list, llvm::dwarf::LocListEncodingString, ----
2919 /* ShouldUseBaseAddress */ true, ----
2920 [&](const DebugLocStream::Entry &E) { 0
2921 DD.emitDebugLocEntryLocation(E, List.CU); 0
2922 }); 0
2923 } 0
2924 ----
2925 void DwarfDebug::emitDebugLocImpl(MCSection *Sec) { 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
2926 if (DebugLocs.getLists().empty()) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
2927 return; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
2928 ----
2929 Asm->OutStreamer->switchSection(Sec); 0
2930 ----
2931 MCSymbol *TableEnd = nullptr; 0
2932 if (getDwarfVersion() >= 5) 0
2933 TableEnd = emitLoclistsTableHeader(Asm, *this); 0
2934 ----
2935 for (const auto &List : DebugLocs.getLists()) 0
2936 emitLocList(*this, Asm, List); 0
2937 ----
2938 if (TableEnd) 0
2939 Asm->OutStreamer->emitLabel(TableEnd); 0
2940 } ----
2941 ----
2942 // Emit locations into the .debug_loc/.debug_loclists section. ----
2943 void DwarfDebug::emitDebugLoc() { 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
2944 emitDebugLocImpl( 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
2945 getDwarfVersion() >= 5 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
2946 ? Asm->getObjFileLowering().getDwarfLoclistsSection() 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
2947 : Asm->getObjFileLowering().getDwarfLocSection()); 0
2948 } 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
2949 ----
2950 // Emit locations into the .debug_loc.dwo/.debug_loclists.dwo section. ----
2951 void DwarfDebug::emitDebugLocDWO() { 0
2952 if (getDwarfVersion() >= 5) { 0
2953 emitDebugLocImpl( 0
2954 Asm->getObjFileLowering().getDwarfLoclistsDWOSection()); 0
2955 ----
2956 return; 0
2957 } ----
2958 ----
2959 for (const auto &List : DebugLocs.getLists()) { 0
2960 Asm->OutStreamer->switchSection( 0
2961 Asm->getObjFileLowering().getDwarfLocDWOSection()); 0
2962 Asm->OutStreamer->emitLabel(List.Label); 0
2963 ----
2964 for (const auto &Entry : DebugLocs.getEntries(List)) { 0
2965 // GDB only supports startx_length in pre-standard split-DWARF. ----
2966 // (in v5 standard loclists, it currently* /only/ supports base_address + ----
2967 // offset_pair, so the implementations can't really share much since they ----
2968 // need to use different representations) ----
2969 // * as of October 2018, at least ----
2970 // ----
2971 // In v5 (see emitLocList), this uses SectionLabels to reuse existing ----
2972 // addresses in the address pool to minimize object size/relocations. ----
2973 Asm->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_LLE_startx_length); 0
2974 unsigned idx = AddrPool.getIndex(Entry.Begin); 0
2975 Asm->emitULEB128(idx); 0
2976 // Also the pre-standard encoding is slightly different, emitting this as ----
2977 // an address-length entry here, but its a ULEB128 in DWARFv5 loclists. ----
2978 Asm->emitLabelDifference(Entry.End, Entry.Begin, 4); 0
2979 emitDebugLocEntryLocation(Entry, List.CU); 0
2980 } ----
2981 Asm->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_LLE_end_of_list); 0
2982 } ----
2983 } ----
2984 ----
2985 struct ArangeSpan { ----
2986 const MCSymbol *Start, *End; ----
2987 }; ----
2988 ----
2989 // Emit a debug aranges section, containing a CU lookup for any ----
2990 // address we can tie back to a CU. ----
2991 void DwarfDebug::emitDebugARanges() { 0
2992 // Provides a unique id per text section. ----
2993 MapVector> SectionMap; 0
2994 ----
2995 // Filter labels by section. ----
2996 for (const SymbolCU &SCU : ArangeLabels) { 0
2997 if (SCU.Sym->isInSection()) { 0
2998 // Make a note of this symbol and it's section. ----
2999 MCSection *Section = &SCU.Sym->getSection(); 0
3000 if (!Section->getKind().isMetadata()) 0
3001 SectionMap[Section].push_back(SCU); 0
3002 } else { ----
3003 // Some symbols (e.g. common/bss on mach-o) can have no section but still ----
3004 // appear in the output. This sucks as we rely on sections to build ----
3005 // arange spans. We can do it without, but it's icky. ----
3006 SectionMap[nullptr].push_back(SCU); 0
3007 } ----
3008 } ----
3009 ----
3010 DenseMap> Spans; 0
3011 ----
3012 for (auto &I : SectionMap) { 0
3013 MCSection *Section = I.first; 0
3014 SmallVector &List = I.second; 0
3015 if (List.size() < 1) 0
3016 continue; 0
3017 ----
3018 // If we have no section (e.g. common), just write out ----
3019 // individual spans for each symbol. ----
3020 if (!Section) { 0
3021 for (const SymbolCU &Cur : List) { 0
3022 ArangeSpan Span; ----
3023 Span.Start = Cur.Sym; 0
3024 Span.End = nullptr; 0
3025 assert(Cur.CU); 0
3026 Spans[Cur.CU].push_back(Span); 0
3027 } ----
3028 continue; 0
3029 } 0
3030 ----
3031 // Sort the symbols by offset within the section. ----
3032 llvm::stable_sort(List, [&](const SymbolCU &A, const SymbolCU &B) { 0
3033 unsigned IA = A.Sym ? Asm->OutStreamer->getSymbolOrder(A.Sym) : 0; 0
3034 unsigned IB = B.Sym ? Asm->OutStreamer->getSymbolOrder(B.Sym) : 0; 0
3035 ----
3036 // Symbols with no order assigned should be placed at the end. ----
3037 // (e.g. section end labels) ----
3038 if (IA == 0) 0
3039 return false; 0
3040 if (IB == 0) 0
3041 return true; 0
3042 return IA < IB; 0
3043 }); ----
3044 ----
3045 // Insert a final terminator. ----
3046 List.push_back(SymbolCU(nullptr, Asm->OutStreamer->endSection(Section))); 0
3047 ----
3048 // Build spans between each label. ----
3049 const MCSymbol *StartSym = List[0].Sym; 0
3050 for (size_t n = 1, e = List.size(); n < e; n++) { 0
3051 const SymbolCU &Prev = List[n - 1]; 0
3052 const SymbolCU &Cur = List[n]; 0
3053 ----
3054 // Try and build the longest span we can within the same CU. ----
3055 if (Cur.CU != Prev.CU) { 0
3056 ArangeSpan Span; ----
3057 Span.Start = StartSym; 0
3058 Span.End = Cur.Sym; 0
3059 assert(Prev.CU); 0
3060 Spans[Prev.CU].push_back(Span); 0
3061 StartSym = Cur.Sym; 0
3062 } ----
3063 } ----
3064 } ----
3065 ----
3066 // Start the dwarf aranges section. ----
3067 Asm->OutStreamer->switchSection( 0
3068 Asm->getObjFileLowering().getDwarfARangesSection()); 0
3069 ----
3070 unsigned PtrSize = Asm->MAI->getCodePointerSize(); 0
3071 ----
3072 // Build a list of CUs used. ----
3073 std::vector CUs; 0
3074 for (const auto &it : Spans) { 0
3075 DwarfCompileUnit *CU = it.first; 0
3076 CUs.push_back(CU); 0
3077 } ----
3078 ----
3079 // Sort the CU list (again, to ensure consistent output order). ----
3080 llvm::sort(CUs, [](const DwarfCompileUnit *A, const DwarfCompileUnit *B) { 0
3081 return A->getUniqueID() < B->getUniqueID(); 0
3082 }); ----
3083 ----
3084 // Emit an arange table for each CU we used. ----
3085 for (DwarfCompileUnit *CU : CUs) { 0
3086 std::vector &List = Spans[CU]; 0
3087 ----
3088 // Describe the skeleton CU's offset and length, not the dwo file's. ----
3089 if (auto *Skel = CU->getSkeleton()) 0
3090 CU = Skel; 0
3091 ----
3092 // Emit size of content not including length itself. ----
3093 unsigned ContentSize = ----
3094 sizeof(int16_t) + // DWARF ARange version number ----
3095 Asm->getDwarfOffsetByteSize() + // Offset of CU in the .debug_info 0
3096 // section ----
3097 sizeof(int8_t) + // Pointer Size (in bytes) ----
3098 sizeof(int8_t); // Segment Size (in bytes) 0
3099 ----
3100 unsigned TupleSize = PtrSize * 2; 0
3101 ----
3102 // 7.20 in the Dwarf specs requires the table to be aligned to a tuple. ----
3103 unsigned Padding = offsetToAlignment( 0
3104 Asm->getUnitLengthFieldByteSize() + ContentSize, Align(TupleSize)); 0
3105 ----
3106 ContentSize += Padding; 0
3107 ContentSize += (List.size() + 1) * TupleSize; 0
3108 ----
3109 // For each compile unit, write the list of spans it covers. ----
3110 Asm->emitDwarfUnitLength(ContentSize, "Length of ARange Set"); 0
3111 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("DWARF Arange version number"); 0
3112 Asm->emitInt16(dwarf::DW_ARANGES_VERSION); 0
3113 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("Offset Into Debug Info Section"); 0
3114 emitSectionReference(*CU); 0
3115 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("Address Size (in bytes)"); 0
3116 Asm->emitInt8(PtrSize); 0
3117 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("Segment Size (in bytes)"); 0
3118 Asm->emitInt8(0); 0
3119 ----
3120 Asm->OutStreamer->emitFill(Padding, 0xff); 0
3121 ----
3122 for (const ArangeSpan &Span : List) { 0
3123 Asm->emitLabelReference(Span.Start, PtrSize); 0
3124 ----
3125 // Calculate the size as being from the span start to its end. ----
3126 // ----
3127 // If the size is zero, then round it up to one byte. The DWARF ----
3128 // specification requires that entries in this table have nonzero ----
3129 // lengths. ----
3130 auto SizeRef = SymSize.find(Span.Start); 0
3131 if ((SizeRef == SymSize.end() || SizeRef->second != 0) && Span.End) { 0
3132 Asm->emitLabelDifference(Span.End, Span.Start, PtrSize); 0
3133 } else { ----
3134 // For symbols without an end marker (e.g. common), we ----
3135 // write a single arange entry containing just that one symbol. ----
3136 uint64_t Size; ----
3137 if (SizeRef == SymSize.end() || SizeRef->second == 0) 0
3138 Size = 1; 0
3139 else ----
3140 Size = SizeRef->second; 0
3141 ----
3142 Asm->OutStreamer->emitIntValue(Size, PtrSize); 0
3143 } ----
3144 } ----
3145 ----
3146 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("ARange terminator"); 0
3147 Asm->OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, PtrSize); 0
3148 Asm->OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, PtrSize); 0
3149 } ----
3150 } 0

3154 const RangeSpanList &List) { ----

3158 llvm::dwarf::RangeListEncodingString, ----
3159 List.CU->getCUNode()->getRangesBaseAddress() || 0
3160 DD.getDwarfVersion() >= 5, 0
3161 [](auto) {}); 0
3162 } 0

3205 static void emitMacroHeader(AsmPrinter *Asm, const DwarfDebug &DD, 0
3206 const DwarfCompileUnit &CU, uint16_t DwarfVersion) { ----
3207 enum HeaderFlagMask { ----
3208 #define HANDLE_MACRO_FLAG(ID, NAME) MACRO_FLAG_##NAME = ID, ----
3209 #include "llvm/BinaryFormat/Dwarf.def" ----
3210 }; ----
3211 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("Macro information version"); 0
3212 Asm->emitInt16(DwarfVersion >= 5 ? DwarfVersion : 4); 0
3213 // We emit the line offset flag unconditionally here, since line offset should ----
3214 // be mostly present. ----
3215 if (Asm->isDwarf64()) { 0

3217 Asm->emitInt8(MACRO_FLAG_OFFSET_SIZE | MACRO_FLAG_DEBUG_LINE_OFFSET); 0
3218 } else { ----

3220 Asm->emitInt8(MACRO_FLAG_DEBUG_LINE_OFFSET); 0
3221 } ----
3222 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("debug_line_offset"); 0
3223 if (DD.useSplitDwarf()) 0
3224 Asm->emitDwarfLengthOrOffset(0); 0
3225 else ----
3226 Asm->emitDwarfSymbolReference(CU.getLineTableStartSym()); 0
3227 } 0

3229 void DwarfDebug::handleMacroNodes(DIMacroNodeArray Nodes, DwarfCompileUnit &U) { 0
3230 for (auto *MN : Nodes) { 0

3232 emitMacro(*M); 0
3233 else if (auto *F = dyn_cast(MN)) 0
3234 emitMacroFile(*F, U); 0
3235 else ----
3236 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected DI type!"); 0
3237 } ----
3238 } 0
3239 ----
3240 void DwarfDebug::emitMacro(DIMacro &M) { 0
3241 StringRef Name = M.getName(); 0
3242 StringRef Value = M.getValue(); 0
3243 ----
3244 // There should be one space between the macro name and the macro value in ----
3245 // define entries. In undef entries, only the macro name is emitted. ----
3246 std::string Str = Value.empty() ? Name.str() : (Name + " " + Value).str(); 0
3247 ----
3248 if (UseDebugMacroSection) { 0
3249 if (getDwarfVersion() >= 5) { 0
3250 unsigned Type = M.getMacinfoType() == dwarf::DW_MACINFO_define 0
3251 ? dwarf::DW_MACRO_define_strx 0
3252 : dwarf::DW_MACRO_undef_strx; 0
3253 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment(dwarf::MacroString(Type)); 0
3254 Asm->emitULEB128(Type); 0
3255 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("Line Number"); 0
3256 Asm->emitULEB128(M.getLine()); 0
3257 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("Macro String"); 0
3258 Asm->emitULEB128( 0
3259 InfoHolder.getStringPool().getIndexedEntry(*Asm, Str).getIndex()); 0
3260 } else { ----
3261 unsigned Type = M.getMacinfoType() == dwarf::DW_MACINFO_define 0
3262 ? dwarf::DW_MACRO_GNU_define_indirect 0
3263 : dwarf::DW_MACRO_GNU_undef_indirect; 0
3264 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment(dwarf::GnuMacroString(Type)); 0
3265 Asm->emitULEB128(Type); 0
3266 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("Line Number"); 0
3267 Asm->emitULEB128(M.getLine()); 0
3268 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("Macro String"); 0
3269 Asm->emitDwarfSymbolReference( 0
3270 InfoHolder.getStringPool().getEntry(*Asm, Str).getSymbol()); 0
3271 } ----
3272 } else { ----
3273 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment(dwarf::MacinfoString(M.getMacinfoType())); 0
3274 Asm->emitULEB128(M.getMacinfoType()); 0
3275 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("Line Number"); 0
3276 Asm->emitULEB128(M.getLine()); 0
3277 Asm->OutStreamer->AddComment("Macro String"); 0
3278 Asm->OutStreamer->emitBytes(Str); 0
3279 Asm->emitInt8('\0'); 0
3280 } ----
3281 } 0

3436 ----
3437 uint64_t DwarfDebug::makeTypeSignature(StringRef Identifier) { 0
3438 MD5 Hash; 0
3439 Hash.update(Identifier); 0
3440 // ... take the least significant 8 bytes and return those. Our MD5 ----
3441 // implementation always returns its results in little endian, so we actually ----
3442 // need the "high" word. ----
3443 MD5::MD5Result Result; ----
3444 Hash.final(Result); 0
3445 return Result.high(); 0
3446 } ----
3447 ----
3448 void DwarfDebug::addDwarfTypeUnitType(DwarfCompileUnit &CU, 0
3449 StringRef Identifier, DIE &RefDie, ----
3450 const DICompositeType *CTy) { ----
3451 // Fast path if we're building some type units and one has already used the ----
3452 // address pool we know we're going to throw away all this work anyway, so ----
3453 // don't bother building dependent types. ----
3454 if (!TypeUnitsUnderConstruction.empty() && AddrPool.hasBeenUsed()) 0
3455 return; 0
3456 ----
3457 auto Ins = TypeSignatures.insert(std::make_pair(CTy, 0)); 0
3458 if (!Ins.second) { 0
3459 CU.addDIETypeSignature(RefDie, Ins.first->second); 0
3460 return; 0
3461 } ----
3462 ----
3463 bool TopLevelType = TypeUnitsUnderConstruction.empty(); 0
3464 AddrPool.resetUsedFlag(); 0
3465 ----
3466 auto OwnedUnit = std::make_unique(CU, Asm, this, &InfoHolder, 0
3467 getDwoLineTable(CU)); 0
3468 DwarfTypeUnit &NewTU = *OwnedUnit; 0
3469 DIE &UnitDie = NewTU.getUnitDie(); 0
3470 TypeUnitsUnderConstruction.emplace_back(std::move(OwnedUnit), CTy); 0
3471 ----
3472 NewTU.addUInt(UnitDie, dwarf::DW_AT_language, dwarf::DW_FORM_data2, 0
3473 CU.getLanguage()); 0
3474 ----
3475 uint64_t Signature = makeTypeSignature(Identifier); 0
3476 NewTU.setTypeSignature(Signature); 0
3477 Ins.first->second = Signature; 0
3478 ----
3479 if (useSplitDwarf()) { 0
3480 MCSection *Section = ----
3481 getDwarfVersion() <= 4 0
3482 ? Asm->getObjFileLowering().getDwarfTypesDWOSection() 0
3483 : Asm->getObjFileLowering().getDwarfInfoDWOSection(); 0
3484 NewTU.setSection(Section); 0
3485 } else { ----
3486 MCSection *Section = ----
3487 getDwarfVersion() <= 4 0
3488 ? Asm->getObjFileLowering().getDwarfTypesSection(Signature) 0
3489 : Asm->getObjFileLowering().getDwarfInfoSection(Signature); 0
3490 NewTU.setSection(Section); 0
3491 // Non-split type units reuse the compile unit's line table. ----
3492 CU.applyStmtList(UnitDie); 0
3493 } ----
3494 ----
